Affordable authentic Japanese bar food. We had delicious sashimi and kushiyaki accompanied by a couple of draft Sapporo and went home satisfied and not-broke.
Try the wagyu burrata, squid ink risotto and finish it off with the chocolate fondant - perfect!

From the folks who brought you Ronin and The Plain; try the drumlets, the fish & chips and the off menu desserts. Just 5 days old but steady showing so much potential. The coffee is also exemplary.
Great coffee at an affordable price.

tips.text: They've gone upmarket. No more $6.50 beef noodles. After ++, now min is about $9, and the qty of beef has shrunk. Kitchen has moved behind so now you don't get to see your beef being cooked.

tips.text: The food here was great. However, the management should relook at the queuing system as there are two queues – one at each entrance.

Wonderful place for lunch or dinner. Great, fresh produce. Chef/owner wants you to eat well! Very affordable. Hearty salads for $8.

tips.text: I love this place. Not sure what the other dude is talking about but portion sizes are huge. I usually get a wrap for lunch and take half of it takeaway and eat it for dinner its so generous. Big ups!

Happy hours daily till 8pm 25% off!

tips.text: Меню небольшое и не очень понятное, особенно если учесть, что от персонала ждать помощи не приходится. Что ж до еды, то она на тройку. Жалко, но и у мэтров гастрономии бывают промахи.

tips.text: Note: The queue at peak hours goes round the side and behind the stall. So don't be too happy when you see "no / short queue" in front of the stall.

Fantastic beef straganoff :)
Good Indian food. They have dum biriyani as well.
